414,IssueCommentEvent,2017-11-29 13:10:07+00:00,68560140,cs01/pygdbmi,5715368,cs01,,,277507802,347855598,"@paulorb the reason for this is because pygdbmi waits for one second (by default) before returning. There is a [while loop](https://github.com/cs01/pygdbmi/blob/master/pygdbmi/gdbcontroller.py#L239) that reads responses until a certain time has passed, which is the wait time you're experiencing. This is by design. See the [documentation](http://grassfedcode.com/pygdbmi/api/pygdbmi.html#pygdbmi.gdbcontroller.GdbController.write). 

You can do something like

```
response = gdbmi.write('next', timeout_sec=0.05)
```

to define how long pygdbmi reads responses from gdb before returning.

@bobthekingofegypt I don't think adding the sleep time where you mentioned will make it run any faster.
",{},OWNER,User,False
