449,IssueCommentEvent,2017-08-15 20:55:32+00:00,5021892,hgrecco/pint,16520296,CalebBell,,,230830792,322586201,"Hi Bloer,
I realize now/agree about the difference between converting and reducing. It would seem to be a great deal of work to implement this as described, but clarifying the behavior to describe it as converting to base units instead of reducing dimensions wouldn't be hard at all. Looking into this further, the test cases added don't describe what should happen when a single quantity is created. I have no personal preference, but either way there should be a test.

I would wager that your desired behavior for ""reducing"" would have more applications than converting everything to a base units. From a chemical engineering perspective, the following is undesirable:

```
>>> from pint import *
>>> u = UnitRegistry(auto_reduce_dimensions=True)
>>> print(5*u.Pa*u.s)
5000.0 gram / meter / second

```",{},,User,False
