692,IssueCommentEvent,2016-12-19 11:58:05+00:00,17250474,szaghi/FoBiS,1661942,szaghi,,,196313705,267947555,"@cmacmackin 

In the just uploaded master branch I have done this improvement. **Backward compatibility broken!** I modified the *old* PreForM.py specific options to make them *general*, namely related to any preprocessor the user select. In particular the old `--preform` switch is now

`-preprocessor` 

It can be used 

+ **without** a subsequent value: in this case PreForM.py is (tried to be) used;
