1343,IssueCommentEvent,2018-04-18 23:31:15+00:00,21006723,pmorissette/bt,166162,brandon-rhodes,,,315674537,382561212,"Okay, I figured it out.

First, ""pandas-datareader"" 0.6.0 doesn't support Yahoo, but the new version will have it working again. So I ran:

```
pip install https://github.com/pydata/pandas-datareader/archive/master.zip
```

Second, it now seems to return a dictionary rather than a plain dataframe, so that I had to adjust this clause:

```
    if field:
        return tmp[field]
    else:
        return tmp
```

so that it instead reads:

```
    if field:
        return tmp['prices'][field]
    else:
        return tmp
```

With those tweaks, I'm now moving again!",{},NONE,User,False
