> Ok, here is the latest. The branch “noshow” on github adds the possibility
> of using “@n” with itemtype “-“ (tasks). @n stands for “do not show"" and
> takes a list of one letter views from a) agenda, d) day (week and month),
> t) tag and k) keyword. For example, “@n a, d” would hide the task from
> agenda, week and month views but would allow it to be shown in tag and
> keyword views. It is not possible to prevent it being shown in path view.
> Thus “@n a, d, k, t” would hide it from all views except path. I’m thinking
> that this would give you the behavior you want without resorting to
> mis-using notes. Let me know.
