> Hi Stanislas
>
> I finally have enough free time to look again into this library, and I'm
> now revisiting open issues. Let me address your concerns by parts:
>
>    - ""# Sometimes two characters are written before the char we want"".
>    The issue was that ToUnicode is stateful and was leaving hanging dead
>    keys for the next call. This has been fixed by calling it twice when the
>    first call reports a dead key. Not elegant, but neither is ToUnicode.
>    - I've made some improvements on how alt gr is dealt with, but it's
>    still a hardcoded 541 value. I would not listen for WM_HOTKEY if I can get
>    away with it.
>    - ""keeps waiting with no output at all ..."": I could not reproduce
>    this error in any of my systems.
>
> The master branch contains many, many improvements, to both high level
> functions and OS-specific backends. I know it's been a long time, but if
