1953,IssueCommentEvent,2015-12-16 18:08:23+00:00,11929631,craffel/mir_eval,3009670,justinsalamon,,,122534292,165197200,"p.s. also, unlike onset eval, if an AME algorithm is slightly off, it will only be marginally penalized (since only a few frames will be incorrect). Adding a tolerance would also be problematic since e.g. imagine an f0 sequence returned by an algorithm that has a few unvoiced frames in the middle, whilst the reference does not. For any sensible tolerance value this would still crop-up as a completely incorrect onset, possibly over-penalizing the algorithm. Not sure it makes sense to evaluate the algorithms on a task they weren't designed to do.",{},,User,False
