2521,IssueCommentEvent,2018-03-08 07:57:59+00:00,78549488,flomotlik/formica,132653,flomotlik,,,303277701,371409347,">However, there is no way to tell what went wrong with the ElasticBeanstalk environment as the rollback process will destroy it.

Yup run into this as well, I typically use awsinfo (another tool I've built) to follow the Elasticbeanstalk events while the deployment happens in case there might be an issue. Another option is simply deploying a very simple version first and then updating it so its definitely there. Not a good option though.

