2602,IssueCommentEvent,2017-12-20 09:48:55+00:00,94133125,metachris/logzero,5230366,carlodri,,,282799180,353016366,"you have precise instructons [here](https://github.com/conda-forge/logzero-feedstock#updating-logzero-feedstock) and [here](https://conda-forge.org/#update_recipe).

In summary, you need to:
* fork the [feedstock repo](https://github.com/conda-forge/logzero-feedstock)
* update the package version tag in `recipe/meta.yaml` (_e.g._ `{% set version = ""1.3.1"" %}`)
* update the package source SHA256 in `recipe/meta.yaml` (_e.g._ `{% set sha256 = ...}`). You can easily copy & paste it from [here](https://pypi.org/project/logzero/#files)
* submit a PR, wait for tests to succeed and merge it",{},NONE,User,False
2608,IssueCommentEvent,2016-01-20 08:33:39+00:00,30484966,michael-lazar/rtv,5026795,michael-lazar,,,124405146,173128368,"Hi Alex! You should sync up with @tyjak, he made a pull request for the same issue a few days ago https://github.com/michael-lazar/rtv/pull/187. Maybe you guys can pool your PR's together and come up with the best solution? To answer your questions:

- I like tyjak's keybinding of <kbd>w</kbd>. I have no strong inclination either way, but I like w because it's easy to type and it's close to the other modifier keys (upvote, downvote, edit, delete, etc.)
- The ""saved"" label should be applied immediately. The trouble is that reddit caches pages every 30ish seconds of so. If you wait for reddit to acknowledge your saved post, it might not show up for a while even if you refresh the page. Check out how I implemented upvote/downvote for reference.",{},,User,False
