2641,IssueCommentEvent,2015-08-30 05:58:32+00:00,7163762,mk-fg/pretty-yaml,227121,mk-fg,,,103862526,136091031,"Yeah, it's a weird constant indeed, thanks for pointing it out.

There's no real formatting going on though, just a decision on which string repr style to use (YAML allows for several).
You probably mean this line: https://github.com/mk-fg/pretty-yaml/blob/5488a55/pyaml/__init__.py#L121

PyYAML has controls for indent/width, which should do what you want, but these keywords weren't passed from `pyaml.dump()` before, which should be fixed in e694fe7 (on PyPI as well).

Now you should be able to do something like: `pyaml.dump(wide_and_deep, width=40)`
width=80 is the default in PyYAML, but might be worth passing it explicitly anyway).

I've added a note on the thing to the readme tricks section (last one): https://github.com/mk-fg/pretty-yaml/#some-tricks
",{},,User,False
