2831,IssueCommentEvent,2018-07-21 04:51:54+00:00,11100375,BoboTiG/python-mss,5691865,HatScripts,,,341323104,406770637,"I've tried to look up ways to get a more specific error, but I'm really not familiar with `ctypes` at all. Could something like [this](https://stackoverflow.com/a/29866855/2203482) work, or is that just for WinDLL?

Also, in case I wasn't clear, the `AttributeError` is raised when `mss.grab` is called and it raises `ScreenShotError('gdi32.GetDIBits() failed.')`, but you caught the `ScreenShotError` and then called `mss.grab` again. Example:
```py
while True:
    try:
        mss.grab(area)
    except mss.exception.ScreenShotError:
        print(""If this happens..."")
    except AttributeError:
        print(""...then this happens on the following while loop iteration"")
```

This could of course be avoided by simply checking `if self._data:` before calling [`del self._data`](https://github.com/BoboTiG/python-mss/blob/master/mss/windows.py#L202).",{},NONE,User,False
