3183,IssueCommentEvent,2017-08-16 23:18:31+00:00,6002572,santoshphilip/eppy,2014885,santoshphilip,,,180913226,322925596,"Some thoughts on moving to JSON formats (seen from the eppy perspective)

Pros:
- Makes the parsing of JDF(IDF) and JDD(IDD) files trivially simple
- lots of advantages for developers of E+. much easier to extend objects
- easier parsing for E+ tool developers.


Cons:
- JDF file is more verbose, making text editing more cumbersome.
- HVACTemplates are no longer supported. 
    - This is a big problem, since this is the simplest direct way to make HVAC systems.
    - Without HVACTemplates, all systems will have to be painstakingly built by hand.
    - there may be a great need to build HVACTemplate functionality in eppy.
- The easier parsing of file is not as useful to eppy, since eppy has a very robust parser.",{},,User,False
