3527,IssueCommentEvent,2018-02-16 06:12:39+00:00,106929485,ikalchev/HAP-python,25887324,ikalchev,,,297612178,366152921,"Hey thanks for contributing! I am happy you liked the project, keep posting issues like these.

About the issue - interesting enough, the CurrentTemperature definition is taken as-is from Apple's HomeKit Dev Kit, i.e. Apple is using 0-100 range as the default as well. But your change makes sense - who wouldn't want to support negative temperatures by default?

What worries me is that as soon as I re-parse the Dev Kit types to include the latest new Chars and Services (there are a few), your change will be ""rolled back"" (see `gen_hap_types.py` at the root of the project). The solution I was thinking about is to have a kind of `overrides.json` file, which will contain ""patches"" for Apple's default min/max values, etc. This file will be integrated as a last step in `gen_hap_types.py`. Thoughts?

In any case, this is good to go, merging!

PS Very nice touch with the absolute zero.",{},OWNER,User,False
