3655,IssueCommentEvent,2017-03-03 00:06:15+00:00,6872298,mwilliamson/spur.py,391876,mwilliamson,,,211409173,283823431,"I wouldn't recommended accessing the internal state of Spur, since that's not guaranteed to work between versions.

If you're using Python 2, you could just be able to do something like:

```python
shell.spawn(cmd, stdout=sys.stdout)
```

In Python 3, `sys.stdout` is a text file, so you'll need to get the underlying buffer:

```python
shell.spawn(cmd, sys.stdout.buffer)
```",{},,User,False
