```fish
$ set GITHUB_TOKEN 1234etc
```
Your snippet still threw exceptions at me at that point. Same error about broken pipes. Then I printed the token to stdout, and it was none! So I logged into a `sh` session, did
```sh
$ export GITHUB_TOKEN=1234etc
```
and your snippet suddenly works. So I looked at the Fish docs and as it turns out, I need to use
