4248,IssueCommentEvent,2017-12-19 17:01:59+00:00,24806180,tariqdaouda/pyArango,7224902,tariqdaouda,,,283163006,352821854,"Hi @Jacobgoss30,

As ArangoDB has no schema validation capabilities, the schema validation is entirely on pyArango's side and ArangoDB is unaware of it.That means that you can usually change it as much as you want without having to worry about the DB. If you had no errors if probably means that everything is running just fine.

The only problems arise when you add in new validation schemes that are not compatible with data already in the DB ex: add a ""Not Null"". In that case you can solve the problem by adding defaults that fit the validation rules.",{},OWNER,User,False
