5251,IssueCommentEvent,2017-10-20 06:41:11+00:00,8490649,Anorov/cloudflare-scrape,7513265,Coriou,,,266658038,338119646,"From the [sqlmap wiki](https://github.com/sqlmapproject/sqlmap/wiki/Usage) : 

```
--cookie=COOKIE     HTTP Cookie header value
--cookie-del=COO..  Character used for splitting cookie values
--load-cookies=L..  File containing cookies in Netscape/wget format
--drop-set-cookie   Ignore Set-Cookie header from response
``` 

This means that the tool supports external cookies, and this how you'll interface it with cfscrape. First, you get the cookies from cfscrape after it has completed the challenge, then you pass them to sqlmap.

An interesting option is `--load-cookies`, which means it would be possible to share a cookie jar between the two tools which sounds like the easiest way to get going.

No demo code though, if you want to run massive penetration testing against hosts you don't have control over, I think you should be able to figure the rest yourself ;)",{},NONE,User,False
