5409,IssueCommentEvent,2015-10-01 03:34:59+00:00,17860497,mattrobenolt/django-sudo,476338,joshkel,,,103778416,144611019,"Regarding the delay, no problem; I'm sorry I didn't reply sooner.

Thanks for the link to pytest and `django_user_model`. Maybe I'm missing something, but I don't see how it would suffice by itself. If I understand correctly, the purpose of `django_user_model` is to handle the difference between `User` on Django 1.4 (because 1.4 doesn't have built-in support for replacing the user model) and `get_user_model()` on 1.5 and above. Instead, the test needs to substitute a custom user model for a single test.

It looks like I could use [TestCase.settings()](https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/1.4/topics/testing/#overriding-settings) plus `django_user_model`, but after looking at this more, I think it's probably easiest to delete some of the hackery and just add a ""pragma: nocover"" to not complain about the Django 1.4 support. Please see my updated PR.

If I'm missing anything, or if there's anything you'd like me to change, please let me know.",{},,User,False
