7164,IssueCommentEvent,2016-02-26 09:32:14+00:00,3526435,incuna/django-wkhtmltopdf,304164,johnraz,55510,incuna,136629624,189188888,"I was more thinking of having something like 
```
render_pdf_from_templates(pages, header, footer, request, cmd_options)
```
where `pages` would be a list of 2 tuples like `[(template, context), (template,context),...]`.
The same principle could be applied to `header` and `footer` params (they could take a two tuple as value).

But if we go this way we should change `render_pdf_from_template` too to apply the 2 tuple thing.

Do you believe this would cover more use cases with this form?

If we decide to break the `convert_to_pdf` signature I think we can consider this, otherwise it should be part of another PR.",{},,User,False
7165,IssueCommentEvent,2015-11-26 20:04:07+00:00,3526435,incuna/django-wkhtmltopdf,451398,powderflask,55510,incuna,97829461,159986895,"No.  This patch (https://github.com/incuna/django-wkhtmltopdf/commit/4b73d48254749bbf08c42126f10b16ac2d71f004) resolved the issue for Python 3 / mod_wsgi < 4.4.14
However, mod_wsgi 4.4.14 + now implements TextIOWrapper interface correctly by supplying a fileno() method, but throwing IOError to indicate it is not valid.   Under new versions of mod_wsgi, even the patch above fails.
I will send a pull-request for a patch that handles all cases -- Python 2 / 3  and variants of mod_wsgi.  Sorry I didn't get to this early.",{},,User,False
