7280,IssueCommentEvent,2016-09-12 17:14:33+00:00,6538922,jquery/jquery-migrate,1758366,mgol,70142,jquery,164320985,246420065,"> I remember thinking about this at the time, the issue with peerDependencies is that npm3 requires you to install them manually and I didn't wan't to do that.

There's no way around that. The purpose of `peerDependencies` is to depend on a package that needs to have one instance and you can't create your own. The correct way to go is to put it both in `devDependencies` and `peerDependencies` (the version range in `peerDependencies` should be more forgiving) and remove from `dependencies`.",{},,User,False
