8361,IssueCommentEvent,2016-07-09 21:07:23+00:00,38108816,biolab/orange3-text,713026,nikicc,555189,biolab,161208078,231555968,"> I used orange GUI for hierarchical clustering on Persian corpora successfully till now. The results are marvelous considering tokenizing was with just \w+ regex or (?=(\w+ \w+)) for n-grams.

For n-grams you can also try the Ngrams widget inside this PR.

> I can do preprocessing with python code fair well, but I don't know how embed python code in orange, or more important how to embed orange in python code :-( , I would be glad to test all you features on Persian corpora.

What I actually meant was that doing preprocessing itself inside Orange might be more challenging for Persian. Did you experiment with Preprocess Text widget? If so, what were the problems? Was there some functionality missing that prevented you to do proper preprocessing?

If Preprocess Text is not appropriate for your needs there is still an other option. You can do it completely manually — and inside Orange — using Python Script widget. Load the data and connect it to Python Script. Here you will do preprocessing as you wish using Python code and then store it to Corpus. The output can then be connected to any other widget just like the output of Preprocess text could be. 

For example tokenizing documents by space could be done like this:

<img width=""755"" alt=""screen shot 2016-07-09 at 23 04 08"" src=""https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/713026/16710289/7b8ce6c8-4629-11e6-9229-901e9e99e844.png"">




 ",{},,User,False
