8419,IssueCommentEvent,2016-08-23 13:00:31+00:00,2625205,robotframework/Selenium2Library,993527,emanlove,574284,robotframework,172474297,241722175,"Funny, I was starting to think, why not, switch over to md for these smaller inner-project documents that are mostly read through Github. [Laughing - @zephraph and I seem to always go in opposite directions]. I would say that for larger more in-depth documentation (generally put into a /doc directory off of root) I would definitely stick to reStructuredText as this is the Python standard and mostly widely used in the Python community.

Really for now the deciding factor would be a debate of maintenance/current effort and forward drive. The forward drive would favor md while the effort to convert over something that is currently doing the job would say leave it be and focus on development. And as you want to get out a release I don't see a compelling and significant reason to spend the time switching over and doing editorial checking.

But I will re-say it (even though I am hesitant too) I'm ok with switching these smaller inner-project documents to md.",{},,User,False
