8846,IssueCommentEvent,2016-06-07 20:17:40+00:00,4978045,Parsely/pykafka,2749029,jianbin-wei,779641,Parsely,153643017,224400809,"In general I think pykafka should handle what are known and pass back what are unknown.

When I shutdown the broker, it causes socket.gaierror.  This error is different from connection refused.  Maybe due to the fact that I am running kafka broker as docker container.  The shutdown causes its removal from network.  In that case, I think pykafka should handle it.  

But when it is not known error, I think it should pass back to caller.  Otherwise the caller would have no chance to catch and handle it.  Once figuring out when that would happen and it is recoverable, I believe pykafka should start handle the exception (it is not unknown anymore).

My 2c.",{},,User,False
