9020,IssueCommentEvent,2016-04-03 17:07:32+00:00,2014929,scikit-image/scikit-image,1315589,soupault,897180,scikit-image,135371491,205010540,"Thanks a lot for the update!

> Also, what exactly is being checked in the ""AppVeyor build"" and ""The Travis CI build""?

Both tools build `skimage` distributables and run all available tests. For Travis, `skimage` is being build with different flags (""defines"") versus different versions of Python.
As long as this PR doesn't include any Cython code, you should worry only about:
- Working {and PEP8 compliant} code;
- Your tests passing.

Regarding the output variables: we should think a bit about the most frequent use case. If user would need mostly `segmentation` variable, we may output only it by default and make other variables available via extra function argument (like, ""extented_output"", `False` by default).",{},,User,False
