9051,IssueCommentEvent,2018-03-23 00:30:28+00:00,2014929,scikit-image/scikit-image,492549,jni,897180,scikit-image,307556486,375501200,"> given that we already implemented and started the deprecation cycle based on reflect, I am not inclined to change it again to edge at this point unless there is a stronger reason to do so.

I agree with this, thanks @grlee77. If we have another core dev on this camp, I'll go ahead and close this.

@not522 Thank you very much for the report. As @grlee77 said, the optimal choice is really use-dependent. For your use, you should use `mode='edge'`. For other uses (for example to expand borders or augment natural image data for neural networks), reflect is a better choice. Therefore I think we will probably leave the default as is.",{},CONTRIBUTOR,User,False
