9159,IssueCommentEvent,2015-07-30 13:19:43+00:00,9252533,numenta/nupic,3386273,david-ragazzi,1039191,numenta,97683090,126320871,"These days I'm making several benchmarkings to test some proposals to improve nupic (OO approach, alternative compilers, etc). One of this is test an old proposal related to use `pypy` as main compiler instead CPython. The fact that I get (very) excellent performance results to a (very) low price: only 1 or 2 lines in SpatialPooler need be refactored due to a numpy function not ported to pypy (yet). I still doesn't test TemporalMemory with pypy but I'm pretty sure that probably no lines will need be changed.

