9246,IssueCommentEvent,2015-07-13 14:39:51+00:00,2562442,mozilla-services/cornice,4029388,tisdall,1066228,mozilla-services,93169723,120952291,"@surabujin - colander is used in this case primarily for validation.  They're accomplishing that with `deserialize(serialize())`.  So, cornice does make calls to both `deserialize` and `serialize`.  If `default` is set to something other than `null` than that element can be missing and the validation will still pass.

To re-iterate, my points are:
 - don't modify existing tests unless it's directly related to the changes you're making.
 - write tests that demonstrate the issue you're trying to fix (they should fail without your fix but pass after the fix is added).",{},,User,False
