9994,IssueCommentEvent,2018-04-14 17:11:03+00:00,3470471,FortAwesome/Font-Awesome,627125,garretwilson,1505683,FortAwesome,145526913,381344297,"This is actually even a greater need now with the release of Font Awesome 5.

Before I was using [Font Awesome 4.7.0 `fa-language`](https://fontawesome.com/v4.7.0/icon/language/) to introduce a Unicode character sequence `U+XXXX`. That was a cute little compact icon.

But the new [Font Awesome 5 `fa-language`](https://fontawesome.com/icons/language?style=solid) glyph is wider and more distracting. (Side note: in general I think having an icon that looks like two icons side by side is not a good idea.)

So in the brands icon set we need the actual [Unicode Consortium logo](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Unicode_Consortium#/media/File:Unicode_logo.svg). See https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Unicode_logo.svg .",{},NONE,User,False
