10094,IssueCommentEvent,2017-12-31 11:36:36+00:00,3470471,FortAwesome/Font-Awesome,7935057,Hi-Angel,1505683,FortAwesome,285239875,354599152,"Ok, I think you're right. For some reason I couldn't make i3bar working with the new naming of fonts, and lack of font-related debug output doesn't help either. However I think Font-Awesome per se is alright because on the linked reddit topic peoples who are using polybar managed to make it working by simply changing the name from FontAwesome to `FontAwesome5Free` and `FontAwesome5Brands`, and the fact it's not working for some app out there is not a concern of a font per se.",{},NONE,User,False
10097,IssueCommentEvent,2018-08-22 08:03:04+00:00,3470471,FortAwesome/Font-Awesome,4432213,matpag,1505683,FortAwesome,304265516,414947553,"I had the same error moving from 5.1.0 to 5.2.0.
At the end the probelm was int the `package-lock.json`, where simply updating fortawesome to 5.2.0 and executing `npm i` didn't update `@fortawesome/fontawesome-common-types` dependency.

I had to manually update it in package-lock.json from 0.2.0 to 0.2.2 and install again, now everything is fine.",{},NONE,User,False
