10396,IssueCommentEvent,2018-08-29 04:53:48+00:00,35882519,zalando/connexion,610121,dtkav,1564818,zalando,348200074,416823851,"Hey @sidhujasminder this is a known limitation of connexion at the moment (but still a major bummer).

I think this will be a backwards-incompatible change because right now the server relies on the `consumes` field in the specification to deserialize the data, and ignores the client's content-type headers. It should be using both. There are probably many users who aren't providing any content-type headers.

I can try to address it in the dev-2.0 branch.

Thanks for raising the issue.",{},COLLABORATOR,User,False
