10499,IssueCommentEvent,2017-01-09 15:39:15+00:00,22877727,irods/python-irodsclient,9340175,pdonorio,1790166,irods,198967902,271316129,"Ok, I brought back what was mistakenly erased.

To run all tests both on password credentials and GSI I had to use my docker configuration, see instructions [here](https://github.com/EUDAT-B2STAGE/docker-images/tree/master/usecases/irodsgsi).

I saved my config.py related, where I have 'rodminer' which is a user with both password and certificate, and with admin privileges on iCAT. You also need to export variables for certificates:
```
# volume with common certificates on icat and client in our docker compose
export X509_CERT_DIR=""/opt/certificates/caauth""
export X509_USER_CERT=""/opt/certificates/rodsminer/userkey.pem""
export X509_USER_KEY=""/opt/certificates/rodsminer/usercert.pem""
