10500,IssueCommentEvent,2016-04-29 16:24:27+00:00,22877727,irods/python-irodsclient,1790152,adetorcy,1790166,irods,150313788,215792694,"I tested this against an iRODS 4.1.8 server as well:
```
>>> path = '/tempZone/home/rods/foo'
>>> obj = sess.data_objects.create(path)
>>> with obj.open('w') as obj_desc:
...     obj_desc.write('blah')
... 
>>> obj = sess.data_objects.get(path)
>>> 
>>> print obj.checksum
sha2:i33xQ9kccW7PpfwXMAIva0IbBc7e6P1SsfxlqWAwrVI=
>>> 
```
Please note that the `acPostProcForPut` rule is triggered when the object is closed, hence the need to refresh the object to get its checksum (`obj = sess.data_objects.get(path)`)",{},,User,False
