10675,IssueCommentEvent,2018-03-02 08:51:58+00:00,46388888,genialis/resolwe-bio,26635159,mzganec,2120224,genialis,301429902,369859827,"Although tempting, the proposed fix is not correct. N/As in the `DESeq2` output arise from the test for outliers based on the Cook's distance. Think of N/A as a gene flag that indicates a likely outlier in one or more samples. The corresponding p-values of such genes are not 1. See also the discussion on [seqanswers.com](http://seqanswers.com/forums/showthread.php?t=45526).

Instead I propose disabling detection of outliers in [deseq.R](https://github.com/genialis/resolwe-bio/blob/master/resolwe_bio/tools/deseq.R#L38) with
`result <- results(dds, cooksCutoff=FALSE)`.

If needed, we can display position of genes with outliers in volcano plot with a different point style.",{},CONTRIBUTOR,User,False
