10753,IssueCommentEvent,2016-04-19 21:03:44+00:00,2915576,tarantool/tarantool-python,495636,bigbes,2344919,tarantool,149578061,212128897,"https://github.com/python/cpython/blob/2.7/Modules/socketmodule.c#L2510-L2511 : 

``` c
    if (!PyArg_ParseTuple(args, ""i|i:recv"", &recvlen, &flags))
        return NULL;
```
as i've guessed.

In python 3.* It's fixed. They use internal number types for this function:

https://github.com/python/cpython/blob/3.5/Modules/socketmodule.c#L2912-L2913

``` c
    if (!PyArg_ParseTuple(args, ""n|i:recv"", &recvlen, &flags))
        return NULL;
```

Since it's `i` - they use 4 bytes signed integer, and it limits recv command to 2^31.

Try to avoid big requests, try to use `limit` and `offset` arguments of select command.",{},,User,False
