10799,IssueCommentEvent,2016-08-03 18:35:07+00:00,6248645,ARM-DOE/pyart,1050278,jjhelmus,2540600,ARM-DOE,167734626,237328670,"Good to hear that the suggestion fixed your issue.

You can clear a plot, or technically the axes, of the last sweep plotted by removing the last item from the axes's `collections` attribute.  For example

``` Python
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
...
# plot the first sweep
display.plot_ppi_map(field, 0, basemap=m)
plt.savefig('sweep_0.png')

# remove the first sweep from the axes
ax = plt.gca()
ax.collections.pop(-1)

# plot the second sweep, do not add another colorbar
display.plot_ppi_map(field, 1, basemap=m, colorbar_flag=False)
plt.savefig('sweep_1.png')
```

This does not seem to work if you use `plt.show()` to pop up a interactive window. I'm not familiar enough with those aspects of matplotlib to know why.",{},,User,False
10800,IssueCommentEvent,2015-05-01 19:51:33+00:00,6248645,ARM-DOE/pyart,1050278,jjhelmus,2540600,ARM-DOE,72507454,98218539,"Some example of the improvements in access time that can be archived by delaying the loading of field data until accessing the 'data' key of the field dictionary when only a single field is to be examined:

### NEXRAD Level II Archive files:

``` Python
In [6]: %timeit radar = pyart.io.read_nexrad_archive('KATX20130717_195021_V06', delay_field_loading=False); radar.fields['reflectivity']['data']
1 loops, best of 3: 1.96 s per loop

In [7]: %timeit radar = pyart.io.read_nexrad_archive('KATX20130717_195021_V06', delay_field_loading=True); radar.fields['reflectivity']['data']
1 loops, best of 3: 943 ms per loop
```

### CfRadial

``` Python
In [8]: %timeit radar = pyart.io.read_cfradial('sgpxsaprrhicmacI5.c0.20110524.015604_NC4.nc', delay_field_loading=False); radar.fields['reflectivity_horizontal']['data']
1 loops, best of 3: 335 ms per loop

In [9]: %timeit radar = pyart.io.read_cfradial('sgpxsaprrhicmacI5.c0.20110524.015604_NC4.nc', delay_field_loading=True); radar.fields['reflectivity_horizontal']['data']
10 loops, best of 3: 57.2 ms per loop
```

Results will vary greatly depending on file content (greater speed ups when the file contains many fields) and hardware especially hard drive speed.  These tests were run on a machine with a non-SSD hard drive.",{},,User,False
