10807,IssueCommentEvent,2015-06-09 15:21:55+00:00,6248645,ARM-DOE/pyart,1050278,jjhelmus,2540600,ARM-DOE,30351418,110400813,"An update.  The  [`np.ma.getmaskarray`](http://docs.scipy.org/doc/numpy/reference/generated/numpy.ma.getdata.html) and [`np.ma.getdata`](http://docs.scipy.org/doc/numpy/reference/generated/numpy.ma.getdata.html) functions work as a reliable method for determining the data and mask from a NumPy **ndarray** or **MaskedArray**.  These are the suggested method to use in Py-ART algorithms which work with data which may or may not be masked, for example field data.  

