11087,IssueCommentEvent,2016-10-20 19:12:16+00:00,16316451,GoogleCloudPlatform/google-cloud-python,242750,tseaver,2810941,GoogleCloudPlatform,183904788,255200096,"@dhermes For queries, the [docs](https://cloud.google.com/bigquery/docs/reference/v2/jobs/getQueryResults#totalRows) say `totalRows` is only present on a page of results if the query has already completed:  we can therefore presume that i will not change.

For tables, the [docs](https://cloud.google.com/bigquery/docs/reference/v2/tabledata/list#totalRows) say only that `totalRows` represents ""[t]he total number of rows in the complete table."" We would have to ask the back-end team whether the `page_token` encodes a ""timestamped"" cursor which would make `totalRows` constant across pages, even if new values were inserted into the table in the meanwhile.",{},,User,False
