11725,IssueCommentEvent,2015-06-05 22:19:39+00:00,21954559,datamade/usaddress,141466,Downchuck,3723931,datamade,62840869,109459646,"Looking further into this, and having implemented, I think that ""normalization"" is really a ""data append"" process. Anything beyond basic translations gets into some complex rule sets.

There are ambiguities that can be cased, such as:
```
""FL"" -> ""Florida"" or ""FL""->""Floor""
```

But when it comes to it, you're trying to land on something standard. Then you need a large data set.
You end up tapping into these two:
```
http://federalgovernmentzipcodes.us/
openaddresses.io
```

And now you're in data-append land.",{},,User,False
