12338,IssueCommentEvent,2016-04-07 15:28:18+00:00,32382669,crossbario/txaio,145599,meejah,5656948,crossbario,146636129,206953041,"Conceivable, it might be possible to add txaio support for some sort of decorator-wrapper over @inlineCallbacks/@coroutine but of course only one at a time. That is, instead of ``@inlineCallback``s or ``@coroutine`` you'd decorate with ``txaio.coroutine`` or similar.

However, we haven't needed this in Autobahn...

Also, I'm not sure how you'd get around the ``yield from`` difference: any ""txaio"" decorator would have to work in Python2.7 with Twisted, so there'd need to be some way to *always* write code with a plain ``yield`` but have it work properly with asyncio in Python3.x -- and I'm not sure if that's possible, so that'd be the place to start ;)

If you really want to try mixing twisted/asyncio I think https://github.com/itamarst/txtulip is the place to start.",{},,User,False
