12541,IssueCommentEvent,2016-08-20 16:30:09+00:00,11589713,deis/deis,12552530,kmala,6117407,deis,172173085,241209582,"> why does a pod get created for each build ? Does the builder is only responsible for receiving push and run the build in an other pod ?

Yes builder just runs a git server and is responsible for receiving the push and run the build in another pod(slugbuilder/dockerbuild) depending on the type of the app being deployed.This way multiple users can deploy different apps simultaneously.
> why the minio is out of storage ? Should I override something to have a bigger volume ? I have plenty of disk space on my k8s nodes.

I think this an issue with the kubernetes not giving enough volume to the docker file system.
https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/issues/14276
https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/issues/25174
> what's going on with the database pod ?

Database is trying to create a bucket for storing the backup but for some reason is failing and i think this might be because of the disk space issue.
> why do I had S3 bucket issues during my build, knowing that I haven't configured object storage as explained in this doc ?

we use minio(https://github.com/deis/minio) for storage which has an s3 compatible api and you see s3 bucket issues as we use s3 api's for interacting with it.

You can check here for some of the prerequisites  https://deis.com/docs/workflow/quickstart/provider/aws/boot/ 
",{},,User,False
