12560,IssueCommentEvent,2015-12-10 14:23:06+00:00,11589713,deis/deis,3778974,sstarcher,6117407,deis,120452036,163633624,"I would not 100% say I have sorted it out ;)

* Older versions of Deis I did have a router problem where the router would write an invalid config and stop writing the config.  Deis 1.10 and prior I believe.  
* A recent issue was I had an app of scale 1 that would sometimes throw an error which would cause the health check to take it out of rotation and taking the app down since nothing was health.  This was resolved by scaling it up to 2+
* Another recent issue was an haproxy node running inside of Deis that 1 of it's 3 backend routes was invalid causing it to intermittently fail.

To track down these problems I would repeatedly curl each Deis router along with the IP:PORT directly of the docker container I was trying to route to.  This allows you to test if the app itself has a problem or if the routing is causing the issue.

To force curl to send the correct host data spoofed you can use.
``` curl -H 'Host: myapp.private' IP_OF_ROUTER```",{},,User,False
