12608,IssueCommentEvent,2017-06-13 19:23:48+00:00,53438969,globus/globus-cli,1300022,sirosen,6120321,globus,225188592,308221629,"I kept meaning to read this and never did. It looks good, and checks out okay.

> I feel like most of the options this issue was created for are now arguments

That may be, but I think `--shared` is a perfect example of something which is technically constrained to be an option, but which we really want only one of. These cases will still exist, and it's nice to be able to respect the fact that if you're specifying certain options more than once, it's probably a mistake.",{},,User,False
12609,IssueCommentEvent,2017-01-25 13:33:30+00:00,53438969,globus/globus-cli,1300022,sirosen,6120321,globus,202935273,275108543,"IIRC, `--max-concurrency`, `--preferred-concurrency`, `--max-parallelism`, and `--preferred-parallelism` are all missing API support.
I think that they are ignored on update, just like `subscription_id`, but given that the docs don't mention this, it's possible that I'm misremembering.


`--subscription` is a bigger issue because it's a piece of administrative functionality -- even if it was in the hosted CLI, it doesn't really belong in a user-facing tool.
I've floated my thoughts on a [plugin architecture](https://github.com/globus/globus-cli/issues/155) to add functions for privileged users, but I also think this could be done in a less general way, tightly scoped to a special `superuser` plugin. (i.e. detect and load a package if it is present).",{},,User,False
