12659,IssueCommentEvent,2018-08-17 11:02:36+00:00,71996613,blue-yonder/tsfresh,96679,earthgecko,6234170,blue-yonder,351498741,413831710,"I was just looking at the code and there has been a change in master relating to
his function in master at:
https://github.com/blue-yonder/tsfresh/commit/48226bade8f5dd65ca021a4977f22ad5dd60769b#diff-6d5c97a0f5c5242f0f8d14214ec0a84eR209

```max_min_difference = max(x) - min(x)``` was changed to:

```max_min_difference = np.max(x) - np.min(x)```

This change was not related to this numpy deprecation that you have encounter,
but related to General performance improvements. (#339)

However it appears as if numpy have now deprecated this in somewhere between
1.10.4 and 1.14.2 so the replacement with ```np.logical_xor(max(x), min(x))```
any replacements will all need to be tested and any other similar functions too.

Thanks for the reporting the issue @hassanshah7866 , perhaps there can be some testing done this
weekend.
