12906,IssueCommentEvent,2017-02-16 14:34:23+00:00,6235174,conda/conda,391586,pvanderlinden,6392739,conda,207776423,280346093,"I think this is related to a bug I forgot to report:
For example, when you have an environment.yml file, and create/update a conda environment with it:
```
name: test
dependencies:
- menpo::opencv3
- redis-py
- python=3.5
```
you will actually install redis from the menpo channel instead of the default. That is why I had to change it into:
```
name: test
dependencies:
- menpo::opencv3
- anaconda::redis-py
- anaconda::redis
- python=3.5
```
Basicly if you specify a package from a channel, it will also try to install all other packages from that repo, even if it is available in the default channels. ",{},,User,False
