12983,IssueCommentEvent,2016-11-21 13:21:36+00:00,16557526,pysam-developers/pysam,10130907,hzpc-joostk,6598771,pysam-developers,183011037,261936920,"@bioinformed At first, many thanks for taking time on this!

So now for your implementation and example. I saved your sample script, customized it so I could easily pass a filepath to a test VCF. This worked:

```
zsh> python test.py my.vcf.gz
Wrote 236 headers + 2768 records
Read 236 headers + 2763 records
```

I tried it using my own script:

```python
# test2.py
import subprocess
import sys

from pysam import VariantFile

with subprocess.Popen(['bcftools', 'view'] + sys.argv[1:], stdin=sys.stdin, stdout=subprocess.PIPE) as proc:
    with VariantFile(proc.stdout) as vcf:
        proc.stdout = None  # Prevent Popen from closing an FD already closed by VariantFile
        for i, rec in enumerate(vcf):
            if i == 5: break
            print(repr(rec), rec.chrom, rec.pos)
```

```bash
zsh> python test2.py my.vcf.gz
zsh> python test2.py < my.vcf.gz
zsh> cat my.vcf.gz | python test2.py
# all above work and output something like
<pysam.libcbcf.VariantRecord object at 0x7f1e6377d630> Chr.1 1068
<pysam.libcbcf.VariantRecord object at 0x7f1e672f55f8> Chr.1 1070
<pysam.libcbcf.VariantRecord object at 0x7f1e6377d630> Chr.1 1072
<pysam.libcbcf.VariantRecord object at 0x7f1e672f55f8> Chr.1 1073
<pysam.libcbcf.VariantRecord object at 0x7f1e6377d630> Chr.1 1078
```

That's great! To prevent unnecessary compression/decompression and VCF←→BCF conversion, I tried passing `-Ou` to the `bcftools` child: `['bcftools', 'view', '-Ou']`

See also https://samtools.github.io/bcftools/bcftools.html#common_options **-O, --output-type** *b|u|z|v*  
and https://samtools.github.io/bcftools/bcftools.html#_performance.

But then all I get is `segmentation fault (core dumped)`. Unless I remove `-Ou` again or change it to `-Ov`. It seems that only plain VCF is supported.

`sys.stdin` works as well, but only with plain VCF:

```python
# test3.py
import sys
from pysam import VariantFile

with VariantFile(sys.stdin) as vcf:
    for i, rec in enumerate(vcf):
        if i == 5: break
        print(repr(rec), rec.chrom, rec.pos)
```

```
zsh> cat my.vcf.gz | python3 test3.py
[1]    11519 broken pipe                       cat  |
       11520 segmentation fault (core dumped)  python3 test3.py

zsh> bcftools view my.vcf.gz | python3 test3.py  # Convert to plain VCF first
<pysam.libcbcf.VariantRecord object at 0x7f1e6377d630> Chr.1 1068
<pysam.libcbcf.VariantRecord object at 0x7f1e672f55f8> Chr.1 1070
<pysam.libcbcf.VariantRecord object at 0x7f1e6377d630> Chr.1 1072
<pysam.libcbcf.VariantRecord object at 0x7f1e672f55f8> Chr.1 1073
<pysam.libcbcf.VariantRecord object at 0x7f1e6377d630> Chr.1 1078

zsh> bcftools view -Ou my.vcf.gz | python3 test3.py  # Convert to uncompressed BCF
[1]    12086 broken pipe                       bcftools view -Ou  |
       12087 segmentation fault (core dumped)  python3 test3.py
```

Could this minor problem be solved? Thanks!",{},,User,False
