13249,IssueCommentEvent,2017-05-23 16:47:21+00:00,4127088,Azure/azure-sdk-for-python,1050156,lmazuel,6844498,Azure,227384275,303462927,"@glaubitz that's an excellent question. I guess it's now possible, but back in time the entire ARM eco-system was in preview (I released 2.0.0 last week, but before that it was 2.0.0rc6 and latest stable was 1.0.0 from August 2015).
So currently, all X.Y.Z versioned packages are in ""azure"" (X != 0), some 0.Y.Z are in ""azure"", but have not yet be confirmed as stable by the team (reading semantic versioning, it's acceptable that 0.Y.Z might introduce breaking changes), and several 0.Y.Z are not in ""azure"" because they are not tested enough, or not stable enough.
In an ideal world, all packages in ""azure"" should be X.Y.Z packages, and not stable should be X.Y.ZrcX.
I will consolidate the packages versioning in the next release to make it more simple to use.
Thanks for the feedback :)",{},,User,False
