13256,IssueCommentEvent,2015-08-27 01:52:23+00:00,4127088,Azure/azure-sdk-for-python,1696845,huguesv,6844498,Azure,102978924,135238380,"We contacted the author of:
https://azure.microsoft.com/en-us/documentation/articles/resource-group-authenticate-service-principal/

and he made some fixes to it (the node CLI section).

I just got it working following the CLI instructions.

The following additional articles were useful in using the CLI:
https://azure.microsoft.com/en-us/documentation/articles/xplat-cli-connect/
https://azure.microsoft.com/en-us/documentation/articles/xplat-cli/

One issue I encountered was that since I have multiple subscriptions on my Azure account, the wrong subscription was active. That active subscription happened to not have a tenant id associate with it, so I kept getting an error:
```
error:   tenantID cannot be null.
```

You can list your subscriptions with:
```
azure account list
```
Then to set the active subscription:
```
azure account set <subcriptionid>
```

After that the instructions worked as expected.  I'll update the readme files later, just be aware that the password you use in the `azure ad app create` command is the `client_secret`, and `client_id` is the ApplicationId.  I don't know if it's possible to get the endpoint from the CLI, I just used the portal for that.
```
auth_token = get_token_from_client_credentials(
    endpoint=<click view endpoints on the portal bottom toolbar and choose OAuth 2.0 Token Endpoint>',
    client_id='<ApplicationId>',
    client_secret='<password>',
)
```

If you get any errors along the way, let me know the details of the error.  I might have just encountered them myself at some point.


",{},,User,False
