13708,IssueCommentEvent,2017-09-21 07:53:23+00:00,33653601,jupyter/notebook,327925,takluyver,7388996,jupyter,247523023,331080757,"There's a special case in the code to interpret `""python""` as the same Python executable which is running the notebook server. So if your notebook server is running on Python 3, any kernel with `""python""` as the first argument will run with that too.

