13747,IssueCommentEvent,2015-07-01 09:19:17+00:00,33653601,jupyter/notebook,466429,frederikhermans,7388996,jupyter,92204376,117557714,"@takluyver You're absolutely right, it should be `pre-wrap` instead of just `wrap`. (Just as `white-space` is `pre-wrap` for all `<pre>` tags, as defined in notebook.less).

But even with `pre-wrap`, the prompt's wrapping behavior is slightly different from the rendered result, because the `<span>` breaks words differently than the `<pre>`. So either we add more CSS to the  `<span>` to get `<pre>`-like behavior, or we replace the `<span>` with a `<pre>` for the prompt. The latter solution seems cleaner to me.

I'll look into it and get back in a day or two.",{},,User,False
