13973,IssueCommentEvent,2018-03-09 17:44:38+00:00,13880738,buildinspace/peru,860932,oconnor663,8107815,buildinspace,303382741,371888214,"You could use the `--no-cache` flag to tell peru to re-fetch the directory. In a way this is similar to how git behaves when you don't have a `rev` specified. The first time you `sync`, it'll talk to the network and fetch the current git `HEAD`. But on subsequent syncs, it won't re-fetch, unless you bust the cache.

That said, `cp` is an undocumented plugin that only exists for testing. Could you say more about what you're using it for? There's a good chance another approach would be better.",{},OWNER,User,False
