14244,IssueCommentEvent,2017-10-01 18:04:52+00:00,24043280,sshuttle/sshuttle,1298987,fkoester,8774006,sshuttle,237429307,333394884,"I think I need to reopen this issue. I just learned the address given above `fe80::1ad6:c7ff:fe61:8043%2` seems to actually be a valid (link-local) IPv6 address according to https://superuser.com/questions/99746/why-is-there-a-percent-sign-in-the-ipv6-address.

And it is also reachable:

```bash
fabian@heisenberg ~ $ ping6 'fe80::1ad6:c7ff:fe61:8043%2'
PING fe80::1ad6:c7ff:fe61:8043%2(fe80::1ad6:c7ff:fe61:8043) 56 data bytes
64 bytes from fe80::1ad6:c7ff:fe61:8043: icmp_seq=1 ttl=64 time=0.167 ms
```

So i guess sshuttle (or the address parsing library) should learn to handle those kind of addresses.

",{},NONE,User,False
