14514,IssueCommentEvent,2016-01-03 20:27:10+00:00,26516210,letsencrypt/letsencrypt,16443496,pseudo2,9289019,letsencrypt,123654034,168538652,"thanks @timir! I've been able to reproduce the scenario. It occurs on an edge case - there exists a http vhost for a domain with a redirection rewriterule and a ssl vhost, for the same domain, doesn't exist. Then the client creates a new ssl vhost and mistakenly puts a redirection rewriterule. 

