14592,IssueCommentEvent,2017-09-13 09:06:25+00:00,56217288,confluentinc/confluent-kafka-python,524990,edenhill,9439498,confluentinc,257174599,329105943,Is there a particular subject/use-case with regards to the configuration dict that you are interested in?,{},MEMBER,User,False
14594,IssueCommentEvent,2018-02-15 14:07:28+00:00,56217288,confluentinc/confluent-kafka-python,524990,edenhill,9439498,confluentinc,295815135,365937072,"Yes, do note that it also accounts for outstanding ops (events) enqueued for the application to poll.
So this value should not be treated as an exact measure of the number of outstanding messages, but rather a level thing which is at least the number of outstanding messages, might be more.",{},MEMBER,User,False
14597,IssueCommentEvent,2016-07-07 19:27:02+00:00,56217288,confluentinc/confluent-kafka-python,524990,edenhill,9439498,confluentinc,164363209,231181848,"You need to call poll() at regular intervals to serve the producer's delivery report callbacks.
Produced messages remain accounted for, even after succesful ack by the broker, until the application's delivery report callback has been called for each message.

poll(0) is a cheap call if nothing needs to be done so it is typically put in the producer loop.

You should typically only call flush() on termination to make sure all outstanding messages are sent.",{},,User,False
