14643,IssueCommentEvent,2018-08-11 17:05:21+00:00,26876372,dateutil/dateutil,1199853,bspeice,9849410,dateutil,349702729,412288461,"Learned something new on PR's today, thanks. Would it be helpful for me to re-open against a feature branch so rebasing on #799 is easier?

Going to take a look at the pyo3 changes more in-depth later, but I agree with the reviewer - I don't think `Copy` is necessary most places you're using it, `Clone` is just fine (see [this answer on SO](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/31012923/what-is-the-difference-between-copy-and-clone#31013156)). Typically `Copy` is used only for primitive types so you don't trigger allocations accidentally for things that only need move semantics.

