The thing is, I don't think either of these things are relevant -- if you take a closer look at what I posted above, the error happens when --outdir is a subdirectory of the current working directory -- I think that is the most relevant thing (and it's not disallowed, is it?).  I just tried running it with a much simpler cwl file, with and without --cachedir, and in both cases the error occurs.  I'm guessing you can get the same behavior with any cwl file.

