15044,IssueCommentEvent,2018-04-27 15:51:52+00:00,103890505,ConsenSys/mythril,8710366,JoranHonig,10818037,ConsenSys,317750045,385013123,"Because analysis will be ran concurrently rubixi would only cause an additional 15 seconds (I don't know if that would be worth it). @birdofpreyru You are right that more extensive testing is better before allowing a merge or something like that. However, if the tests can be built to test some functionality in less time then that should be preferable imo. Because this allows developers to be more active in running and changing the testbase.

