15267,IssueCommentEvent,2016-08-18 14:16:27+00:00,32148457,core-api/python-client,647359,tomchristie,11457133,core-api,171706493,240736332,"The CoreJSON spec documents this here: http://www.coreapi.org/specification/encoding/#document

If the CoreJSON encoding includes a url then that is used as the URL of the document. If it does not then the URL from which it was requested may be used.

The way to handle this is to ensure that the server sets the URL of the document appropriately. Eg don't set it at all development (allow whatever host/port it's being run on), and only set it to the canonical API url in staging/production environments.",{},,User,False
