15319,IssueCommentEvent,2015-09-06 17:54:47+00:00,32944298,Z3Prover/z3,3085284,NikolajBjorner,11668813,Z3Prover,104961814,138104174,"> Maybe I should see how fast a naive bisection using the stable release of Z3 would be. 

It all depends on how your constraints end up being solved. WIth the optimization features, I added several transformations and features to support PB constraints. There is both pre-processing and a dedicated PB theory. The PB theory compiles cardinality costraints to circuits, but only when the constraints from those inequalities are used in several conflicts. It contains some very modest cutting plane reasoning as well. But many constraints can also directly be converted into SAT without overhead and the pre-processor does some efforts to detect this and determine when this is the case.
Finally, if the optimization objective is over 0-1 variables or over Booleans, then the back-end engine is based on max-sat. 
You can run Z3 with ""verbose"" mode set on (from python you can call set_param(verbose=10) to have Z3 display some selected information what it is doing. You can also extract statistics after the satsifiability call to get a profile of which steps it did. It requires some idea of the code modules to deduce anything from it, e.g., if it says it is using anything with ""arith"", then you are using the simplex solver, on the other hand if it mentions ternary clauses, then it is using pure SAT solving (and max-sat).
 ",{},,User,False
15322,IssueCommentEvent,2017-06-20 19:50:25+00:00,32944298,Z3Prover/z3,511795,delcypher,11668813,Z3Prover,236606199,309870131,"@wintersteiger 

Here is a standalone program that reproduces the crash

```c++
#include ""z3.h""
#include <assert.h>
#include <stdlib.h>
#include <stdio.h>

extern ""C"" void errorHandler(Z3_context ctx, Z3_error_code e) {
  printf(""Z3 error: %s\n"", ::Z3_get_error_msg(ctx, e));
  abort();
}

int main() {
  Z3_config cfg = ::Z3_mk_config();
  Z3_context ctx = ::Z3_mk_context_rc(cfg);
  ::Z3_del_config(cfg);
  ::Z3_set_error_handler(ctx, errorHandler);
  // Parser simple query
  Z3_ast constraint =
      ::Z3_parse_smtlib2_string(ctx, ""(declare-fun x () (_ BitVec 32))\n""
                                     ""(assert (= x (_ bv0 32) ) )\n"",
                                /*num_sorts=*/0,
                                /*sort_names=*/0,
                                /*sorts=*/0,
                                /*num_decls=*/0,
                                /*decl_names=*/0,
                                /*decls=*/0);
  ::Z3_inc_ref(ctx, constraint);
  printf(""Loaded constraint: %s\n"", ::Z3_ast_to_string(ctx, constraint));

  // Check top level expr is application
  assert(::Z3_is_app(ctx, constraint));

  // Get the application
  Z3_app asApp = ::Z3_to_app(ctx, constraint);
  unsigned numArgs = ::Z3_get_app_num_args(ctx, asApp);
  assert(numArgs == 2);

  // Get first arg
  Z3_ast firstArg = ::Z3_get_app_arg(ctx, asApp, 0);
  // Print first args
  ::Z3_inc_ref(ctx, firstArg);
  printf(""first arg: %s\n"", ::Z3_ast_to_string(ctx, firstArg));

  // Check that the first arg is an application
  assert(::Z3_is_app(ctx, firstArg));
  Z3_app firstArgasApp = ::Z3_to_app(ctx, firstArg);

  // Get Z3_func_decl of application
  Z3_func_decl fnDecl = ::Z3_get_app_decl(ctx, firstArgasApp);
  ::Z3_inc_ref(ctx, ::Z3_func_decl_to_ast(ctx, fnDecl));
  // Check fnDecl takes no arguments
  assert(::Z3_get_domain_size(ctx, fnDecl) == 0);

  // Get sort of fnDecl's range
  Z3_sort rangeSort = ::Z3_get_range(ctx, fnDecl);
  ::Z3_inc_ref(ctx, ::Z3_sort_to_ast(ctx, rangeSort));
  assert(::Z3_get_sort_kind(ctx, rangeSort) == Z3_BV_SORT);
  printf(""first arg funcDecl range sort: %s\n"", ::Z3_sort_to_string(ctx, rangeSort));

  // Now convert the funcDecl to an AST (legal) and ask its sort
  Z3_ast fnDeclAsAST = ::Z3_func_decl_to_ast(ctx, fnDecl);
  // FIXME: Z3 will crash when we ask for the sort of the fnDeclAsAST
  Z3_sort fnDeclAsASTSort = ::Z3_get_sort(ctx, fnDeclAsAST);
  ::Z3_inc_ref(ctx, ::Z3_sort_to_ast(ctx, fnDeclAsASTSort));
  // What should this be?
  assert(::Z3_get_sort_kind(ctx, fnDeclAsASTSort) == Z3_BV_SORT);

  // Clean up
  ::Z3_dec_ref(ctx, ::Z3_sort_to_ast(ctx, fnDeclAsASTSort));
  ::Z3_dec_ref(ctx, ::Z3_sort_to_ast(ctx, rangeSort));
  ::Z3_dec_ref(ctx, ::Z3_func_decl_to_ast(ctx, fnDecl));
  ::Z3_dec_ref(ctx, constraint);
  ::Z3_dec_ref(ctx, firstArg);
  ::Z3_del_context(ctx);
}
```

Note I'm currently using an old version of Z3 ( 1db07f1189d6560316537ec4822d41e84f0a7105 ). I'm upgrading now to test with the latest build.",{},,User,False
