15621,IssueCommentEvent,2016-07-26 22:21:04+00:00,40328394,angr/angr,2498805,rhelmot,12520807,angr,167725194,235424129,"This isn't any error in analysis, just that we don't support this syscall yet. (it looks like on arm, syscall 122 is `uname`).

We're very busy with the CGC right now, so we can't address this for the next few weeks, but it should be relatively straightforward for you to implement your own `uname` syscall SimProcedure and add it to the appropriate lists! Just look at `angr/simos.py` and search for `SimLinux`, then add an appropriate procedure in `simuvex/procedures/syscalls`.

