15703,IssueCommentEvent,2016-07-11 00:40:16+00:00,18188537,dronekit/dronekit-python,7077857,peterbarker,12973369,dronekit,164665417,231620807,"On Sun, 10 Jul 2016, Ahmed Agbabiaka wrote:

> @janthony i can confirm. the same script that runs on the computer connects
> to solo and runs just fine. if i move that script to solo and run it, the
> script can't connect and times out. the error occurs if i run the script
> directly via python script.py or via solo script pack.
> 
> via solo script run
> Exception in thread Thread-2 (most likely raised during interpreter
> shutdown):
> Traceback (most recent call last):
> File ""/usr/lib/python2.7/threading.py"", line 551, in bootstrap_inner
> File ""/usr/lib/python2.7/threading.py"", line 504, in run
> File ""/log/solo-script/env/lib/python2.7/site-packages/dronekit/mavlink.py"",
> line 166, in mavlink_thread_out
> : 'NoneType' object has no attribute 'error'
> Exception in thread Thread-1 (most likely raised during interpreter
> shutdown):
> Traceback (most recent call last):
> File ""/usr/lib/python2.7/threading.py"", line 551, in __bootstrap_inner
> File ""/usr/lib/python2.7/threading.py"", line 504, in run
> File ""/log/solo-script/env/lib/python2.7/site-packages/dronekit/mavlink.py"",
> line 201, in mavlink_thread_in
> File ""/log/solo-script/env/lib/python2.7/site-packages/dronekit/__init.py"",
> line 1311, in listener
> : 'NoneType' object has no attribute 'monotonic'


OK, so sadly these exceptions don't indicate the source of your issues.

Note the message ""during interpreter shutdown"", and ""'Nonetype' 
object...""; the ""None"" objects there are python modules.  These errors 
occur because the main thread is busy deconstructing itself and the 
interpreter, but the mavlink threads are still running.

These threads should *really* be shut down nicely before we quit, but 
aren't.

Nobody has gone and fixed that as by the time you get them your program 
has finished and it is just messy.  OTOH, it does lead to distractions 
from the real issue - like the one you're facing.

Could you give me the exact incantation of solocli you're using, please?


Peter

",{},,User,False
