15727,IssueCommentEvent,2018-06-20 12:45:23+00:00,16469697,mps-youtube/mps-youtube,1438488,Razesdark,12987682,mps-youtube,329029454,398735695,"Oh yeah, its super easy to identify a channel id and act accordingly.

I'm against using `userpl` because I think it muddies its function by having it work different with one kind of input compared to another. Who would find it natural to search by  *channel_id* using the command `user`. I think the natural expectation of user and userpl is to supply a username and get the results based on that. And we should keep it like that. 

In an example where a user would get all its information from within mpsyt they would have to run the `channels` command to get the channel id, then `user` or `userpl` to use it, that sounds kind of unintuitive to me.

I can see the argument that a layman would not make the distinction between a user and a channel. I would assume that most people think of a channel's name when they see the current `user` command and gets confused why its not working as intended. I wouldn't be opposed to catch both channel names and usernames by the user function as long as the command would react similar in both cases.",{},CONTRIBUTOR,User,False
