15836,IssueCommentEvent,2015-12-11 11:49:17+00:00,43645564,ganga-devs/ganga,1102021,rob-c,13271048,ganga-devs,119954094,163920026,"After a lot of staring at the code and fixing performance/functionality bugs in the Registry I've come to the conclusion that a lot of the functions were based upon the idea of object inspection to determine things like if an object has been loaded from disk or not.
This was unfortunately failing to do any form of caching due to a hand full of minor looking long-standing bugs.

I've changed the registry to keep track internally of which jobs it has loaded and store their ```_registry_id``` internally.
This has been implemented slightly in a slightly hap-hazard way with a lot of old code/functionality/checks still in place.
As the code in the release/6.1.14 branch is in a working state I aim to release without any major work and will attempt to clean up the tracking of job 'load'-ing within both the Registry and Repository layers as part of 6.1.15

I had to implement this in order to allow for dirty objects to exist in memory without being replaced by a historic version of the object from disk as was observed quite often.

I'm planning to add a simple function within the GangaObject (or Registry) to determine if a Job has been fully loaded or not according to the information stored in the registry and repository. This would allow us to make some simple integration tests around the lazy-loading.",{},,User,False
