15893,IssueCommentEvent,2017-06-12 18:03:18+00:00,31315021,Kinto/kinto,83972,mostlygeek,13413813,Kinto,234776370,307869605,"Schema migration should be explicit, separated and not default. It is better to have migration and server startup as two discrete functions. Using `migrate-and-start` as a default is convenient during development but is too risky for production. 

For ops, code deployments and schema changes are usually discrete steps. Deployment are either: 

1. Update the schema, old code continues working. Deploy new code.
2. Deploy new code, continues working with old schema. Update the schema. 

",{},,User,False
