16170,IssueCommentEvent,2016-07-05 19:57:06+00:00,43852872,PulpQE/pulp-smash,1012989,Ichimonji10,14839747,PulpQE,161209365,230585087,"This test passes, but it doesn't actually test whether the `packages_directory` feature works or not. The problem lies with this snippet of code:

```python
packages_locations = get_locations(self.responses['publish2_xml'])
for location in packages_locations:
    self.assertEqual(os.path.dirname(location), 'Packages')
```

This bit of code assumes that several `packages_locations` have been found. However, due to the way `get_locations` is implemented, `packages_locations` is an empty list.

I believe the fix is to use different namespaces in the XPath expressions. I'll try it out tomorrow, and if it works, will use the fix in a follow-up commit.",{},,User,False
