four locations. But no luck. It would have been an ugly solution anyway but
I wanted to get it working and sort out why not later. I don't remember if
I actually tried adding the location to LOAD_LIB_PATH. But I was getting
tired at the end of a long day (Italy time).

This isn't that big a deal, most of the stuff I am trying to do is
with/will be with live video feeds or videos and signals/feedback as i
build my robot. I was trying to use gym as a sandbox, er, well, a gym I
guess but I can always train like Rocky instead of Drago. Since I have to
use video capture and synchronize it with pwm signals anyway, there isn't
much difference in programming except for actively controlling the game, no?

Speaking of that, do you have canned sequences to download?, like a dataset
of video frames sequenced with actions and rewards? It would be interesting
to see how much you could learn just by being a passenger instead of a
driver. Given the right sequences, I think it would train just as well and
would really cut down on the overhead in industrial applications.

Also, since I am up early and seemingly have time, aren't y'all coming out
with a new gym and universe?

Thanks for the response and sorry to have been so verbose,

John

