16334,IssueCommentEvent,2016-03-27 00:46:02+00:00,1843992,jazzband/django-pipeline,451612,fdintino,15129049,jazzband,143091678,201964521,"There is a fork of slimit that has fixed that failing test case ([see here](https://github.com/lelit/slimit/commit/e8331659fb89e8a4613c5e4e338c877fead9c551)). As I see it, you have two options: you could include the patch for this unit test in your debian package (using quilt, perhaps) or you could include all of the changes in [lelit’s fork](https://github.com/lelit/slimit/) as patches to the upstream. Whatever you decide to do in preparing the debian package for slimit, I don't think it's all that relevant to this project. If the concern is that you want to build all the dependencies of pipeline for a debian package, you are welcome to omit slimit from that package since it is only an optional dependency. Use ``tox`` in the test phase of your debian package build to avoid having to create a debian package for slimit in order to run the unit test.

It is true that the slimit unit tests do not appear to be compatible with python 3. In particular they use the `ur""string""` for the failing test case you've pasted above. But slimit itself is indeed compatible with python 3, even if one of its unit tests is written in such a way that it fails in python 3. So I don't see a reason to disable slimit in this package for python 3.",{},,User,False
16336,IssueCommentEvent,2016-06-17 13:31:56+00:00,1843992,jazzband/django-pipeline,451612,fdintino,15129049,jazzband,101456098,226769370,"@tobz This PR isn't being ignored, it's on me actually to finish it. I have some work I haven't pushed out yet that allows for sourcemaps for the post-processors that support it, but getting those sourcemaps to concatenate in the compressor step has proved challenging, specifically for javascript. uglifyjs does not support multiple input sourcemaps, nor does closure compiler. One option is to concatenate the sourcemaps in python (the source map spec is not all that complicated) and then pass a single input sourcemap to uglifyjs, but when I attempted that the performance isn't great. I'll work a bit more on it and perhaps leave multilevel sourcemap support for a future pull request.",{},,User,False
