16412,IssueCommentEvent,2018-05-21 17:08:11+00:00,91379993,tensorflow/tensorboard,710113,nfelt,15658638,tensorflow,324964630,390718645,"I actually have seen this crop up before, though it's generally been hard to reproduce.

I think a sufficient fix would be adding another set of locks, one per value of `PluginEventAcccumulator._plugin_to_tag_to_content` (where the value is a dict of tag to content).  Then we acquire the relevant lock:

1) when adding a new tag to a tag-to-content dict:
https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorboard/blob/6924af8f1cf935ece8ebc7cdf9af917c1220dbda/tensorboard/backend/event_processing/plugin_event_accumulator.py#L342-L347
2) when fetching the tag-to-content dict for a given plugin:
https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorboard/blob/6924af8f1cf935ece8ebc7cdf9af917c1220dbda/tensorboard/backend/event_processing/plugin_event_accumulator.py#L242-L258

I think this shouldn't be too much of a performance hit, hopefully less than a deepcopy on every read, which I don't think would 100% prevent the issue (since I don't think deepcopy is atomic in python, so it could still hit the race condition, there's just a smaller window for it).",{},COLLABORATOR,User,False
