16509,IssueCommentEvent,2016-06-23 21:06:59+00:00,55808787,openthread/openthread,16142208,jwhui,16142269,openthread,162018918,228184029,"The intent of the API was to have the client provide the storage needed for storing netif addresses.  The advantage of having the client provide the memory is that OpenThread itself does not have to be configured to support a certain number of addresses.  The `cli.cpp` is closest to that, the only issue is that `cli.cpp` does not check to make sure that the static struct was already added.

The address pool/link-list approach is least appealing to me.  If we go with OpenThread-allocated netif structures, then we might as well have a fixed array and save the cost of storing/maintaining pointers.",{},,User,False
