I encode characters 128-255 from e.g. CP437 -> UTF-8 to build the encoding tables, then encode back based on the tables only. Ie, iconv never sees UTF-8 user input.

Again, I'm not done but I've pushed what I've got so far to my fork. I've patches the encoding to work as described (encoding with a dictionary, one character at a time), and confirmed that the Greek and Vietnamese text now work.

Travis CI indicates that this has broken some tests, so I'll update those and file a pull request to your fork next time I'm online.",{},,User,False
