* The protected header is a JSON Encoded array, the reason why it is not a dict is that if you want identical outcomes out of 2 invocations you need to pass in a string that cannot change arbitrarily, dict's order is not guaranteed. However I can see how it may halpe to allow a dict, I will add code to accept a dict() if the user passes one in.
