17070,IssueCommentEvent,2016-07-11 18:50:02+00:00,26516210,certbot/certbot,6504915,bmw,17889013,certbot,164898154,231828519,"So I couldn't help myself and just finished detectiving. Here's what happened in chronological order:

1. Friday, July 1st, lint tests passed on #3234 ([source](https://travis-ci.org/certbot/certbot/jobs/141754392)).
2. Friday, July 8th, at 21:09 UTC, lint tests ran and passed on #3261 ([source](https://travis-ci.org/certbot/certbot/jobs/143441170)).
3. Friday, July 8th, at 23:06 UTC, #3234 was merged with `master`.
4. Friday, July 8th, at 23:59 UTC, #3261 was merged with `master`.
5. Saturday, July 9th, at 00:18 UTC, the combination of the two PRs ran in Travis for the first time and failed ([source](https://travis-ci.org/certbot/certbot/builds/143476883)).

To solve this problem would require all PRs to be up to date with `master` (or force Travis tests to run on every PR every time `master` changed). This probably isn't worth the effort, at least at this time, so I'm closing this issue.",{},,User,False
