18018,IssueCommentEvent,2018-06-26 07:42:01+00:00,48593532,tensorpack/tensorpack,1381301,ppwwyyxx,25570510,tensorpack,333559117,400211855,"I don't mind moving the implementation of `TFRecordData` into `load()`.

The only benefit is that `TFRecordData` is for reading data with a user-defined decoder. i.e., we have one API that reads an arbitrary tfrecord, and one API that's a dataflow deserializer, and they share code. Here they are named `TFRecordData` and `TFRecordSerializer.load` respectively.",{},COLLABORATOR,User,False
18019,IssueCommentEvent,2018-07-07 07:06:02+00:00,48593532,tensorpack/tensorpack,1381301,ppwwyyxx,25570510,tensorpack,339111225,403194542,"You can use StagingInput.
I think originally they have not seriously tested such features, just like many other ""fancy"" features in tensorflow that does not work.
You can use GraphProfiler to profile. It works for all types of input.
You can use ProfileContext in your own code. You do not need to touch tensorpack source code.",{},COLLABORATOR,User,False
18020,IssueCommentEvent,2018-08-19 13:15:51+00:00,48593532,tensorpack/tensorpack,30048368,Dataphz,25570510,tensorpack,351895904,414127127,"Thank you for your apply, here is the issue:

1. What you did:
[train command, in order to transfer/finetune] 
