18211,IssueCommentEvent,2018-08-09 13:32:02+00:00,141175642,MouseLand/suite2p,3935246,marius10p,28845184,MouseLand,348729220,411758166,"A lot of these neuropil ROIs were due to simultaneous extraction in the first iteration, which did not allow the neuropil model to adapt to the ROIs (see issue #39 ), We fixed this by imposing an upper bound on how many cells can be extracted per iteration. 

There are still some ROIs that look messy, but they tend to be the same ones as before, and can be cleaned up with the classifier. If anything, there are fewer non-cell ROIs. 

The only issue is still that sometimes there might not be enough neuropil pixels if extraction is too dense. We will treat dense extraction separately (issue #46)",{},CONTRIBUTOR,User,False
