18292,IssueCommentEvent,2018-08-11 05:03:23+00:00,102692863,onnx/onnx,1100089,yinghai,31675368,onnx,349687434,412251225,"This will likely have problems as protobuf has a global registry based on proto file name. If you have two `.so` file that contains `onnx.pb.cc`, this issue will happen. The trick we do is to define a different namespace for onnx when used in third-party and rely on onnx's CMakefile to do the symbol replacement and renaming. Here is an example:

https://github.com/onnx/onnx-tensorrt/blob/fa0964e8477fc004ee2f49ee77ffce0bf7f711a9/CMakeLists.txt#L93-L97",{},COLLABORATOR,User,False
