18465,IssueCommentEvent,2018-07-07 09:08:46+00:00,80946973,lark-parser/lark,731464,erezsh,38646335,lark-parser,339099377,403200987,"Hi,

It sounds like an interesting project! 

I think you've stumbled into an unflattering bug in my implementation. The grammar loader compiles

    [""new""] atom_expr ""("" [arguments] "")""  -> funccall

Into

    ""new"" atom_expr ""("" [arguments] "")""  -> funccall
    | atom_expr ""("" [arguments] "")""  -> funccall

Which (I assume) triggers the safe-guard against defining two rules for the same alias.

Honestly, I'm not sure if this safe-guard is even necessary. And if it is, I need to fix the implementation.

So thanks for bringing this to my attention!

Meanwhile, the following rewrite should work, with the exact same effect:

```ruby
    ?atom_expr: funccall
          | atom_expr ""["" subscriptlist ""]""        -> getitem
          | atom_expr ""."" NAME                     -> getattr
          | atom

    funccall: [""new""] atom_expr ""("" [arguments] "")"" 
```

Good luck, and let me know if you run into any other difficulty.",{},MEMBER,User,False
